<HEADLINE>
FT  22 MAY 93 / Finance &amp; The Family: Scottish Widows bond reissued - At a
Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Scottish Widows has made a new issue of its Monthly Income Bond, which was
criticised by some advisers when launched last year. As before, the bond
consists of an annuity and a personal equity plan. The annuity pays the
income - equivalent to a net 9.11 per cent per annum on the total invested -
while the Pep is designed to grow to repay the annuity. But there is no
guarantee that it will do so - the capital value of the units in the Pep
will need to grow at 7.75 per cent per annum for this to be achieved - so
this is far from a risk-free investment. It is good to see that Scottish
Widows' brochure makes this very clear.
</TEXT>
