<HEADLINE>
FT  22 MAY 93 / Finance &amp; The Family: Gold price riding a speculative
rollercoaster - At a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Gold prices had a topsy-turvy week with the US dollar price touching Dollars
384.50 a troy ounce on Wednesday, its highest level since the panic buying
just after the start of the Gulf War in January 1991.
The price of gold has rebounded from a seven-year low of Dollars 327 an
ounce in London on the first trading day of 1993. The rise during the past
four weeks has been partly inspired by high-profile investors Sir James
Goldsmith, the Anglo-French financier, and George Soros, the US investment
fund manager.
However, the gold price fell back from the Wednesday peak, with some
investors taking profits, and dropped to around Dollars 373 an ounce on
Friday.
