sizeable tap on the growing corporate market. Companies have increasingly
been turning to bonds to raise funds because of the weak equity market and
because bank finance is more expensive.
Alcatel Alsthom, the Paris-based telecommunications and transport group,
said a ADollars 500m domestic commercial paper programme would go towards
working capital used throughout the Asia-Pacific region, Reuter reports from
Sydney.
