Pounds 574,000 for the closure of Barnum's.
Capital expenditure amounted to Pounds 6.6m (Pounds 9m), but tighter
controls on working capital had resulted in a reduction in bank borrowings
to Pounds 16.7m (Pounds 17.8m).
A final dividend of 0.75p (nil) makes an unchanged total for the year of
1.1p. Although not fully covered by earnings of 0.84p (1.24p), the directors
said the payment was appropriate as action had been taken to deal with the
loss-making businesses and further cost reductions were being introduced.
