His father and grandfather were partners in the bank and his elder brother,
Sir Howard, spent a couple of years there before joining S G Warburg.
However, John Guinness is not the family's sole representative in the bank,
now owned by Japan's Bank of Yokohama.
Tim Guinness, 45, joint managing director of Guinness Flight Asset
Management, has kept the family name alive, but he's a descendant of the
brewing side.
