<HEADLINE>
FT  21 MAY 93 / Technology: Mixing up a time saver - Worth Watching
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DELLA BRADSHAW
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Builders and do-it-yourself enthusiasts could save both time and money with
a collapsible cement mixer, designed by a former engineer from Watford.
David Gawron's patented Gizmix replaces the traditional mixer's steel drum
with a synthetic rubber bag inside a web of telescopic tubular rods.
Packaged with the motor the mixer can be stored in a box in the corner of a
workshop or garage.
Because it is light enough to carry, it can also be taken to the upper
stories of a high-rise building without the need for a winch.
Once in production, the Gizmix should cost less than Pounds 100 to buy.
Gawron: UK, 0923 776 747.
